1. CRM Life Cycle

CRM Life Cycle shows the journey of a customer from first contact to long-term relationship.

Stages: Reach, Acquisition, Conversion, Retention, Loyalty

Live Example - Nike:

Reach        Nike shows Instagram ads to fitness lovers
Acquisition  Student signs up and gets 10% off first order
Conversion   Student gets cart reminder email and buys shoes
Retention    Nike sends feedback form, workout tips, recommendations
Loyalty      Customer joins Nike Membership, earns points, refers friends


2. Similarities Between CRM and ERP

CRM manages customers and sales
ERP manages internal operations like inventory, HR, finance

Common Points:
Both are business management systems
Both store data in one central place
Both automate manual tasks
Both help in decision making through reports
Both improve business efficiency
Both can be integrated with each other

Example: A company using Salesforce as CRM and SAP as ERP can share
customer orders, billing data and inventory status automatically.


3. Types of CRM and How to Choose One

Types of CRM:

Operational CRM   focuses on automating sales, marketing and support
                  Example: Salesforce, HubSpot

Analytical CRM    focuses on analyzing customer data and trends
                  Example: Zoho CRM Analytics, SAP CRM

Collaborative CRM focuses on team communication and coordination
                  Example: Microsoft Dynamics 365

Criteria for Choosing a CRM:

Business Requirements   choose based on size and complexity
Ease of Use             should be simple for employees to learn
Cost and Budget         consider subscription, setup and training cost
Customization           should support custom fields, reports, workflows
Integration             should connect with email, ERP, social media
Scalability             should grow with the business
Security                data encryption, access control, backup
Customer Support        good documentation and live support
Mobile Access           should work on mobile devices
Reporting               should provide dashboards and sales analytics

Example:
A startup may choose HubSpot because it is simple and affordable
A large company may choose Salesforce because of advanced features


